From: CARL
Date: OCTOBER 2,1983 1:42
Greg,

  This time, I think I've found a >bug< in UNDELETE!!

If you have a file which has been .TMP-ified, and also bit(8) of
.RBLIC (the license word) is set (this means it's a TMP file), then
Un-deleting the file works fine.  BUT, when you LOGOUT or GFD away
the TMP bit is still set, so... the file goes away!!!

Solution:  UNDELETE should also clear the TMP bit in .RBLIC if it
           is set on a file which is being undeleted.
/Carl


