From: CARL
Date: DECEMBER 14,1983 23:18
New (CARL)LOGON version 1A(70).

It contains a new switch:  /INFO  which modifies /STATUS and thus
needs to be specified prior to the /STATUS switch.  It takes any or
all of the following modifiers:

  /INFO:arg     or     /INFO:(arg,arg,arg,...)

  DAYTIME      prints the date & time
  FRAME        prints the frame number
  PORT         prints TTYnnn
  NETWORK      prints node-line, eg 2242-17
  LOAD         prints system load as percentage
  RESPONSE     prints netork turn-around response time
  MONITOR      prints monitor name from CONFIG
  PROCESSOR    prints processor type, KA-10,...,FOONLY
  MEMORY       prints size of physical memory
  STATES       prints the states word (schedule) if non-zero

  ALL          prints all of the above (default)
  NONE         prints nothing

I've added the /INFO switch to KEN & TSUCOOP's SWITCH.INI and
left it out of Adele's (to show that complete omission is the
same as /INFO  or  /INFO:all.

/Carl


